<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-3878] Compile error in TSSLSocket.cpp with new OpenSSL [CRYPTO_num_locks]</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-3878</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In TSSLSocket if use new OpenSSL library (downloaded and builded from git) will be compile error.&lt;br/&gt;
That because CRYPTO_num_locks is now macro-call instead of function.&lt;br/&gt;
THRIFT -also from git repo (master).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So I simply fix that:&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;#ifdef CRYPTO_num_locks&lt;br/&gt;
  mutexes = boost::shared_array&amp;lt;Mutex&amp;gt;(new Mutex&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;CRYPTO_num_locks()&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;);&lt;br/&gt;
#else&lt;br/&gt;
  mutexes = boost::shared_array&amp;lt;Mutex&amp;gt;(new Mutex[ ::CRYPTO_num_locks()]);&lt;br/&gt;
#endif&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;VS2013&lt;br/&gt;
Thrift from git repo, SHA-1: 5a3f855b4e6882184f13c698855c877241144a12 (master)&lt;br/&gt;
OpenSSL from git repo (master).&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
